---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import { brand } from '../lib/content';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy policy | CrossCoders" description="How CrossCoders collects, uses and protects your data.">
  <PageHero eyebrow="Legal" title="Privacy policy." cta={false} />
  <section class="psec">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <p style="color:var(--ink-mute)">Last updated: 24 June 2026. We handle personal information in line with South Africa's POPIA (and the GDPR where it applies). Kingdom Come Foundation's registration is in progress (CIPC name reservation 9461002404); we'll update our registered details here once it's finalised.</p>
      <h2 class="serif">Who we are</h2>
      <p>This site is operated by <b>CrossCoders</b>, a Christian software studio, on behalf of the <b>Kingdom Come Foundation</b> (in formation) — its non-profit arm. For any privacy matter, our Information Officer is <b>Daniel Jenkins</b>, reachable at <a href={brand.contactHref} style="color:var(--forest-deep)">{brand.email}</a>.</p>
      <h2 class="serif">What we collect</h2>
      <p>Only what you give us: details submitted through our contact, application and support forms (name, email, phone, organisation and message). When you give a gift, we also record your name, email, the amount, and how you choose to be shown as a benefactor. Your card details are entered on Paystack's secure, PCI-compliant checkout and <b>never reach us</b>. We don't use tracking cookies or track you across the web.</p>
      <h2 class="serif">How we use it</h2>
      <p>To respond to your enquiry, review applications, process your gift and send your receipt, and — only if you opt in — email you a build's progress. We use it to run the Foundation and improve the site. We never sell your data, and we never use it to train AI models.</p>
      <h2 class="serif">Who we share it with</h2>
      <p>Only the providers we need to run things, under appropriate agreements: <b>Paystack</b> (payments), <b>Brevo</b> (transactional email) and <b>Cloudflare</b> (site delivery). Donation records are stored on our own secured server. Your <b>email is never shown publicly</b> — the benefactor board only shows the display name you choose, or "anonymous".</p>
      <h2 class="serif">How long we keep it</h2>
      <p>Donation and financial records are kept for as long as the law requires. Other personal information is kept only as long as we need it to help you, and then deleted.</p>
      <h2 class="serif">Your rights</h2>
      <p>You can ask us to access, correct or delete your information, or object to its use, at any time — just email <a href={brand.contactHref} style="color:var(--forest-deep)">{brand.email}</a>. If you're in South Africa and we can't resolve a concern, you may also lodge a complaint with the <b>Information Regulator (South Africa)</b>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
